  "name": "Luke 6:27–49",
  "localizedName": "Luke 6:27–49",
  "content": [
    {
      "tiptap": {
        "type": "doc",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus taught that God’s children should share, give freely and forgive others. Life in God’s kingdom includes loving not only family and friends but even enemies. And it includes God’s children being humble and recognising their own mistakes."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus described a person’s sin like pieces of wood in their eyes. People must deal with their own sin first before they point out the sins of others. Jesus didn’t want people’s "
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "marks": [
                  {
                    "type": "resourceReference",
                    "attrs": {
                      "resourceId": "108419",
                      "resourceType": "BiblicaStudyNotesKeyTerms"
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "text": "hearts"
              },
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": " to be full of evil desires. He wanted them to be full of God’s goodness instead. That way they would be like healthy plants that bear good fruit."
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Jesus taught that those who don’t follow God’s ways are foolish. Not following God is like building a house that will be destroyed. Those who listen to Jesus and obey him are wise. They are building a house that will last."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
